    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-07-28T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-07-28T04:00:00-05:00" n="296"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d296">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/9021: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-07-28T18:00:00+09:00"
                            >July 28, 1937—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received July 28—6:45 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>231. My 229, July 28, 5 [<hi rend="italic">4</hi>] p.m.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>Domei has issued a statement to the effect that I called this morning on
                        the Minister for Foreign Affairs to make inquiry with <pb facs="0293"
                            n="286" xml:id="pg_286"/> regard to the situation in North China. I
                        assume that the Minister for Foreign Affairs has in this instance deemed it
                        expedient not to disclose the actual purpose of my call (see my telegram No.
                        223, July 22, 7 p.m., paragraph 6). I shall not issue correction to the
                        press unless directed by you to do so.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>Fleisher<note n="2" xml:id="d296fn2">Wilfred Fleisher, Tokyo correspondent
                            of the <hi rend="italic">New York Herald Tribune</hi>.</note> has
                        telephoned to New York the text of a statement issued this morning by the
                        Foreign Office setting forth reasons for abandonment by Japan of hope for
                        peaceful settlement of the North China incident.</item>
                </list>
                <p>Repeated to Nanking.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
